  <section class="section">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head section__head--left content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">What Is Dryer Vent Cleaning?</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Why It Matters and Why Our Process Works</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="split-grid content-grid">
        <div class="rich-text">
          <p>
            Dryer vent cleaning is the cleaning of the dryer exhaust line from the back of the
            dryer to the exterior of the home.
          </p>
          <p>
            According to NFPA data, over 17,000 structural fires occur annually from dryer fires,
            and failure to clean dryer vents is a leading cause. Lint buildup also forces longer
            run times, increases utility cost, and can elevate carbon monoxide and fire risks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="notice-box">
          <h3>Why Is Our Process The Best?</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            {processHighlights.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card-grid" style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        {processCards.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <div class="card-icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
              <ServiceIcon variant={item.icon} />
            </div>
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head section__head--left content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">Project Gallery</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Residential Dryer Vent Cleaning in the Field</h2>
      </header>

      <ImageCarousel
        id="residential-dryer-gallery"
        label="Residential dryer vent project gallery"
        items={galleryItems}
        fit="contain"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">What To Expect From Competitors</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Common Issues with Shortcut Methods</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="info-card-grid">
        {competitorMethods.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p><strong>Problems:</strong> {item.problems}</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Risks:</strong> {item.risks}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="notice-box" style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        <h3>What To Look for in a Professional Service</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          {professionalServiceChecklist.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="u-container split-grid">
      <article class="notice-box">
        <h3>Dryer Vent Rodent Covers</h3>
        <p>
          Bird/rodent guards help keep pests out of vent terminations, but the cover type and
          installation method matter.
        </p>
        <ul class="feature-list" style="margin-top: var(--space-s);">
          <li>Metal covers typically last 2 to 4 years longer than plastic.</li>
          <li>Plastic can dry rot faster under direct sun exposure.</li>
          <li>Termination design must still maintain proper dryer exhaust airflow.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="notice-box">
        <h3>Clogged Vent Consequences</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          {ventConsequences.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-s);">
          As part of home maintenance, clean your lint trap between cycles and schedule annual
          professional dryer vent cleaning.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">Our Dryer Vent Cleaning Process</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Step-by-Step</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="info-card-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));">
        {workflowSteps.map((step) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{step.title}</h3>
            <p>{step.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="notice-box" style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        <h3>Why Our Dryer Duct Cleaning Stands Out</h3>
        <p>
          We disconnect the dryer from the vent line when needed to ensure 100% negative suction,
          then clean with proper vacuum and agitation tools designed specifically for dryer duct
          systems. This removes lint thoroughly, reduces clog risk, and avoids the mess and
          limitations of leaf blowers or drill-brush shortcut methods.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">Dryer Vent Cleaning FAQs</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Answers to Common Safety and Code Questions</h2>
      </header>

      <FaqAccordion items={faqItems} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head section__head--left content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">Dryer Vent Repairs / Installs</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Bring Vent Systems Back To Code Compliance</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="rich-text">
        <p>
          Dryer vents often require repair over time. Pipes can loosen, sag, or disconnect,
          especially after roof replacement. When that happens, lint and moisture can accumulate in
          attics or walls. Hygienic Air provides comprehensive repair and install services so dryer
          systems exhaust properly to the outside.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-card-grid" style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        {repairTopics.map((topic) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{topic.title}</h3>
            <p>{topic.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="notice-box" style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        <h3>Signs of Disconnected Vents</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          {disconnectedVentSigns.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        <ImageCarousel
          id="residential-dryer-repairs-gallery"
          label="Residential dryer vent repair examples"
          items={repairsGallery}
          fit="contain"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--deep-blue">
    <div class="u-container split-grid service-inline-grid">
      <article class="service-inline-copy">
        <h3>Give the Dryer Some Space with Dryerbox</h3>
        <p>
          The Dryerbox recessed exhaust receptacle allows dryer placement closer to the wall without
          crushing the transition hose or restricting airflow. This supports safer, roomier, and
          more efficient laundry layouts.
        </p>
        <ul class="feature-list" style="margin-top: var(--space-s);">
          {dryerboxBenefits.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </article>

      <figure class="service-inline-media">
        <Image
          src={residentialDryerboxProductImage}
          alt="Dryerbox product and recessed dryer vent receptacle illustration."
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="u-container">
      <header class="section__head content-stack">
        <p class="section-topper">Dryerbox Exhaust Receptacle</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Safer, Roomier, and More Efficient Homes</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="rich-text" style="max-width: 70ch; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p>
          In traditional installations, flex duct bends and kinks create friction, trap lint, and
          increase fire risk. Dryerbox creates a cleaner in-wall connection that protects the hose,
          improves airflow, and helps your appliance run more efficiently.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-l);">
        <ImageCarousel
          id="residential-dryer-dryerbox-gallery"
          label="Dryerbox and in-wall connection examples"
          items={dryerboxGallery}
          fit="contain"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ContactOptionsSection />

  <Lightbox slot="after-body" />
</SiteLayout>
